p: We combined previous data (testosterone levels and laparoscopy results) collected 1998–2002 [ 34] with data collected 2003–2007. To determine if there was a significant difference in sex ratio (% females) among years and 5-cm size classes (SCL) ranging from 40.0–75.9 cm, we used a contingency table analysis [ 41]. In addition, we computed binomial confidence intervals on the proportion of females for each year and size class.
